Here are the SDK commands you'll use immediately:

* atlas-run   -- installs this plugin into the product and starts it on localhost
* atlas-debug -- same as atlas-run, but allows a debugger to attach at port 5005

Full documentation is always available at:
https://developer.atlassian.com/display/DOCS/Introduction+to+the+Atlassian+Plugin+SDK

Used manuals:
https://developer.atlassian.com/server/jira/platform/creating-a-custom-field-type/
https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA043/How+to+create+a+new+Custom+Field+Type
https://community.atlassian.com/t5/Answers-Developer-Questions/Jira-7-Plugin-sample-jira-custom-field-example-tutorial-jira/qaq-p/481919
https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRASERVER-2734?focusedCommentId=18269&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels%3Acomment-tabpanel
https://developer.atlassian.com/server/jira/platform/creating-a-custom-field-in-jira/

P.S.
If you want to see rendered wiki content in issue navigator, use Atlassian Wiki-renderer in Default Field Configuration.
Last comment size can be changed in field description (default is 90).
